        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"317929\">Derek Rhodes</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/113489-new-members/topic/How.20to.20learn.20the.20group.20theory.20in.20lean4/near/510086387\">发言道</a>：</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Hi Marcus, I'm not an expert, but I am learning about groups with Lean4 at the moment. Here are some of the resources that I've found to be helpful.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://hrmacbeth.github.io/math2001/03_Parity_and_Divisibility.html#modular-arithmetic-theory\">⮺ Mechanics of Proof, Section 3.3 : Modular arithmetic: theory</a></p>\n<p>(some group theory introductory material uses modular arithmetic, so it's good to know how to prove those types of problems)</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.ma.imperial.ac.uk/~buzzard/xena/formalising-mathematics-2024/Part_A/section05groups/groups.html\">⮺ Formalising Mathematics, Section 5 : An introduction to group theory</a></p>\n<p>(Kevin Buzzard has <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=myPZ7D7xyvs\">videos</a> that go along with these worksheets)<br>\n<a href=\"https://github.com/ImperialCollegeLondon/formalising-mathematics-2024/tree/main/FormalisingMathematics2024/Section05groups\">section 5 on github</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://lean-lang.org/doc/reference/latest//Basic-Types/Subtypes/#Subtype\">⮺ The Lean Language Reference, Section: Subtypes</a></p>\n<p>(I've found that subtypes can be helpful for representing some group examples)</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathematics_in_lean/C08_Groups_and_Rings.html#monoids-and-groups\">⮺ Mathematics in Lean: Chapter 8.1, Monoids and Groups</a></p>\n<p>(MiL has some more info on groups earlier in the book, try the search feature to find everything)</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>thank you so much.</p>",
